GOALS

On demand static HTML file generation from git repository

management of the blog


FEATURES

* Pretty Print URLS
    We can pull the url from the file name or perhaps from some header data

* scan directories
* use the git log data to determine when it was last updated / published

/index.html is generated based on the index.html template
/feed.atom is generated based on the reed.atom template

all other posts are generated from the post.html template with the structure

/<year>/<month>/<day>/<slug>/index.html

where the date is grabbed from git or the header and
slug comes from header, or slugged first line or filename
